                            Preamble

The vyAI Social Commons 1.0 License is a free, open-source license designed to ensure the software remains accessible for social and community projects, while restricting its use in purely commercial software products.

This license grants the freedom to share, modify, and use the software for a wide range of applications, including integration into physical hardware products. However, it prevents the software from being sold as a standalone product or offered as a commercial "Software as a Service" (SaaS). This approach aims to foster innovation in the physical world and support community-driven initiatives, without allowing the core software to be monetized directly.

The precise terms and conditions for copying, distribution, and modification follow.

            TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR COPYING, DISTRIBUTION AND MODIFICATION

0. Definitions.

"This License" refers to version 1 of the vyAI Social Commons 1.0 License.

"The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this License. Each licensee is addressed as "you". "Licensees" and "recipients" may be individuals or organizations.

"To "modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the work in a fashion requiring copyright permission, other than the making of an exact copy. The resulting work is called a "modified version" of the earlier work or a work "based on" the earlier work.

"A "covered work" means the unmodified Program or a work based on the Program.

"To "propagate" a work means to do anything with it that, without permission, would make you directly or secondarily liable for infringement under applicable copyright law, except executing it on a computer or modifying a private copy. Propagation includes copying, distribution (with or without modification), making available to the public, and in some countries other activities as well.

"To "convey" a work means any kind of propagation that enables other parties to make or receive copies. Mere interaction with a user through a computer network, with no transfer of a copy, is not conveying.

"Software as a Service (SaaS)" refers to a model where a covered work is hosted by a party and provided to customers over a network, typically on a subscription or fee basis, without conveying a copy of the software itself.

"Physical Product" refers to a tangible, physical hardware item (e.g., robots, wearables, custom devices) that is sold to an end-user and in which the Software is embedded or integrated.

